# The `RangeTy` Struct Reference

<DoxygenPage pluginConfig={pluginConfig}>

## Description {#details}

Helper to represent an access offset and size, with logic to deal with uncertainty and check for overlapping accesses.

  labels = {["inline", "static"]}>
Comparison for sorting ranges.

Returns true if the offset of <code>L</code> is less than that of <code>R</code>. If the two offsets are same, compare the sizes instead.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/ipo/attributor-h/#l00301">301</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/ipo/attributor-h">Attributor.h</a>.

## Public Static Attributes

### Unassigned {#a5960fe0f64e0af63e9cbddb4ab880b7f}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype={<>int64&#95;t llvm::AA::RangeTy::Unassigned = std::numeric&#95;limits&lt;int32&#95;t&gt;::min()</>}
  labels = {["constexpr", "static"]}>
Constants used to represent special offsets or sizes.

<ul>
<li>We cannot assume that Offsets and Size are non-negative.</li>
<li>The constants should not clash with <a href="/docs/api/structs/llvm/densemapinfo">DenseMapInfo</a>, such as EmptyKey (INT64&#95;MAX) and TombstoneKey (INT64&#95;MIN). We use values &quot;in the middle&quot; of the 64 bit range to represent these special cases.</li>
</ul>

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/ipo/attributor-h/#l00315">315</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/ipo/attributor-h">Attributor.h</a>.
